OL,7,FSecondly, Mr Warmington says there is
OL,8,Fevidence the Post Office may have
OL,9,Fmisled the courts by presuming sub-
OL,10,Fpostmasters were guilty and not
OL,11,Fproperly investigating their case.
OL,13,F"When those first interviews take
OL,14,Fplace in the branch, and the person
OL,15,Fsaying: 'I've been telling the
OL,16,Fhelpdesk for the last six months that
OL,17,FI've got this bloody difference'," he
OL,18,Fsaid.
