OL,7,FMr Warmington makes it clear to the
OL,8,FPost Office General Counsel that there
OL,9,Fis clear evidence Alison Hall could
OL,10,Fwell be innocent.
OL,12,FHe said: "When you get to the Alison
OL,13,FHall case...the key question is going
OL,14,Fto be why did the investigation team
OL,15,Fproceed to a prosecution for false
OL,16,Faccounting when the underlying cause
OL,17,Ffor that without much doubt, was that
OL,18,Fshe got in a complete mess over
OL,19,Fscratch cards when Post Office Ltd
OL,20,Fknew that there was a huge problem
OL,21,Fwith reconciliation of scratch cards.
